    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that feels so forced. like its just a coping mechanism we made up to keep from losing our minds. if \"love and art\" are just chemical reactions in a temporary biological shell, then they aren't actually real in any objective sense. when the lights go out, none of it stays. it's all just noise.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
