      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is valid to feel that reducing emotions to biology dismisses the profound experience of connection, even though the underlying processes are indeed chemical. This struggle between objective truth and subjective experience is a core theme in existential philosophy, often leading to the realization that \"reality\" is defined not just by what exists physically, but by how we inhabit it. Many people find comfort not in denying our limitations, but in embracing the paradox of being temporary beings who create meaning where there otherwise seemed to be nothing.",
