      "content": "You are describing the concept of acceptance, which philosophers like Kazuo Ishiguro or Søren Kierkegaard saw not as defeat, but as the only way to live without self-destructive anger toward the void. Given the universe's indifference, forcing a grand, heroic struggle can indeed feel exhausting and counterproductive. Ultimately, finding peace might mean stopping the futile fight for an objective point and instead accepting that the only \"reward\" is the experience of living itself, without the pressure to conquer anything.",
